value: Breeds on the northeast coast of Siberia, northwest coast of Alaska and on St. Lawrence Island. Winters chiefly in the Aleutian Islands.
refer: Peter's Checklist of the Birds of the World

value: Arctic tundra in lowland marsh areas, generally not far from the coast, commuting to upland areas to forage; winters in salt-water areas along reefs and rocky beaches.
br coastal tundra lakes, lagoons.wintrocky seashores, estuar mudflats
